></TR></TABLE><table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top BACKGROUND= http://www.thegamevine.com/~Elegant_Rogue/shanks/blbgrnd2.gif><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BACKGROUND= http://www.thegamevine.com/~Elegant_Rogue/shanks/blbgrnd2.gif><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiamwotan.showPublicProfile>I am Wotan</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global Patron</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>6/23/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>1:48:37 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My take on loot and scoot</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have been following loot-n-scoot since I heard of it, with the following exceptions:<br>
<br>
- Slain via exploit (casting through walls, training, zone-camp, bind-rush, corpse camp, ...)<br>
- /ooc abuse<br>
- Attacked while engaged with npc<br>
<br>
In all of the above situations I treat the person with no more courtesy than I would an npc. <br>
<br>
Notes: <br>
-If I run from a fight and my opponent is forced to cast through walls by my action, this is not an exploit.<br>
-If I run to a zone from a fight and killed while zone ping-ponging, this is not zone-camping<br>
-If I am attacked and <b>then</b> I engage a mob, this does not mean my opponent should stop.<br>
-Slaying someone repeatedly at bind point/corpse who refuses to lootnscoot, is <b>not</b> bind/corpse camping<br>
-I am rather fond of the zone-log as a way of conceding defeat without being looted.  This may change with coin-loot, but in the meantime, I consider myself banned for an hour after the zone-log.<br>
-if attacked in a hunting zone such as befallen, and I am forced to zone   outside where I am slain, I consider myself banned for one hour from the zone in contention (befallen).  <br>
<br>
This is my own personal take on fair-play, I enjoy good spirited competition, but I can be downright nasty when messed with.  I dont expect everyone to follow my way, but I just want to be clear what I mean when I say I support loot and scoot. <br>
<br>
</font><P><b>Wotan</b>  Shaman Elder of the <a href="http://galaxy.apropos.org/shanks">Shanks</a> <br>

