Also when do shanks kill other players? random or just planed raids? or when one enters our home land <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiamwotan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>I am Wotan</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Council of Elders</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>7/12/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>8:42:21 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Wotan_Rogue/mask2a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: My take on loot and scoot</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Loot and Scoot is self-imposed attempt to create meaningful consequences for defeat in PvP.  Basically, most of the roleplaying, fair-minded (probably the minority) guilds have adopted this policy.  Basically, after being slain in a PvP fight, you concede the zone to the victor for a period of at least one hour.  <br>
<br>
This policy also has support from the guides.  Corpse-camping and bind-rushing (illegal and unsportsmanlike tactics) are defined as slaying someone at their corpse/bind point without giving them a chance to leave.  You are not required to allow medding, tolerate smack-talk, etc.  In general it is also good form to not slay someone on corpse run, unless they are trash-talking, or bind-rushing. <br>
<br>
Keep an eye out for me ingame Rogasmo.  I have a minion in Halas that can bring ya into the fold.  <br>
